The paper deals with channel estimation for wireless communication systems, which is a common topic in the information theory (cs.IT) and communication (cs.COMM) sub-categories. The use of compressive sensing (CS) is a key aspect of the paper, which is also a common topic in the signal processing (cs.SI) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The paper also proposes a low-complexity algorithm, which is relevant to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
